						<span>Introduction of Course</span><br/><br/>

						Learn the important techniques of Computer Science Engineering at CGC Landran and build your Career. Computers are used in almost every aspect of our lives these days. The computer industry is one of the fastest growing segments of our country and that growth promises to continue in future as well. An engineering degree in Computer Science and Engineering (CSE) equips you with strong practical and theoretical knowledge of computer software and hardware.<br/><br/>

						<span>Future of CSE Engineers</span><br/><br/>
							 Computer engineering is considered to be one of the fastest growing professions worldwide. Strong employment growth combined with a restricted supply of qualified professionals foresees incredible employment prospects in this field.<br/>
							 Computer engineers have brilliant career prospects in diverse areas like information security, sales user support, software development and programming, system and network administration, research and development, project management, database management, data protection, consulting, market research, software and hardware management, marketing, controlling and information research etc.<br/><br/>
 
 						<span>Eligibility Criteria for Getting Admission in CSE Branch at CGC Landran</span><br/><br/>
 						To get Admission in the best CSE Engineering College of Punjab then you must have 10+2 with Mathematics and Physics are compulsory subjects with one of these following subjects - Computer Science, Bio-technology, Chemistry, Biology is eligible to pursue the B.Tech course. <br/>
 						Those students who have cleared diploma in any engineering trade from the Sant Longowal Institute of Engineering and Technology (SLIET) Longowal or Punjab State Board of Technical Education or from any other State Board of Technical Education or two years certificate course from SLIET are eligible to pursue the bachelor's course in any chosen stream.<br/><br/> 

						<b>Benefits of Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science &amp; Engineering</b>
						<ul >
    					<li>The course is based upon the aptitude and inclination of students to focus on one of the disciplines rising from this mother discipline.</li>
    					<li>This course promises a real-life experience in the field as Research &amp; Development project give a possibility to specialize in specific technologies.</li>
    					<li>Computer engineering graduates get high salary packages and job vacancies are available in India and abroad as well.</li> 
						</ul><br/><br/>
  						
  						<span>Admission Procedure</span><br/><br/>
 						Admission is carried out on the basis of JEE rank for Punjab domiciles and for students belonging to other states through online counseling carried out by PTU, Jalandhar. 66.6% seats make the state quota while 33.3% seats in each discipline are reserved for management quota. Admission seats are to be filled on the basis of merit of 10+2/JEE marks. 
